main event: A civilian observed an orange colored object in the western sky on the night of October 27, 1965, which was concluded to be Venus.
interesting points: The object was compared to Venus but appeared larger than the planet,The object was seen at about 12 degrees high in the west,The sighting lasted until the object twinkled and disappeared,The conclusion indicated it was likely an astronomical observation,The report is part of Project Blue Book which investigated UFO sightings.
sighted object: an orange colored object in the sky
witness description: A civilian and his father both witnessed the sighting.
